$interpreted: Dagger: What happened? Is it enemy ambush?!
Dumb Bear Soldier: Oh, hi, Dagger. It's you.
Dagger: Don't give me that "hi" nonsense!  Were you trying to blow up kitchen!?
Dumb Bear Soldier: Eh? Why would I blow up kitchen?
Dagger: I never said you were actually trying to blow up kitchen!
Dumb Bear Soldier: But didn't you ask me just now if I was trying to blow up kitchen!?

Dagger: Forget it, pretend I ask nothing.
What exactly are you doing here?

Dumb Bear Soldier: Oh, since Christmas right around corner, 
I want to bake cake for wife.
Dumb Bear Soldier: But... why would flour explode? How strange...
Dagger: Chri.... what?  What's that word you just mumbled?
Dumb Bear Soldier: How could you not know about Christmas! It's famous! I thought only nerd bears who stay in caverns don't know about it.
Dagger: Just tell me what that thing is!!
Dumb Bear Soldier: Legend has it the holy warrior Vendacti was born on 25th of Snow Month.
Dumb Bear Soldier: That day was later known as Christmas. To celebrate, people give presents to people they care about on this day.
Dagger: What does human holiday have to do with us Bears?
Dumb Bear Soldier: No matter human or Bear, getting present is always a happy thing, right? At least that's what I think.

Dumb Bear Soldier: You like that princess, don't you?
Why not use this opportunity to make a cake for her too?
Dagger: W... b, bastard! W... who... who said that I like her!?

Dumb Bear Soldier: Eh? So you don't like that princess?
Back then, you were working your butt off trying to save her. Really thought you have feelings for her...

Dagger: I... I do not!
I will not give her cake... or present!
Dagger: By the way, I think I just smelled something weird...

Dumb Bear Soldier: Crap! I burnt it again!!
OWW! That's hot!
Dagger: So getting present will make anyone happy? ......
Dagger: Whew, finally found a bag to store the presents.
Dagger: What 're you doing, you damn exploding mushrooms!
Dagger: Good thing I returned just in time, or else they would've stolen everything!
Dagger: Dumb Bear didn't mention how many presents to give either. This amount should be enough, right?

Dumb Bear Soldier: You like that princess, don't you?
Why not use this opportunity to make a cake for her too?
Dagger: I... I'm not giving her present because I like her!
Dagger: It's just... I hope she can be a bit happier. After all, she kinda went through lot of tough things not too long ago...
Furygrowl: So you are here. Been looking for you for a while.
Furygrowl: This pile of stuff... could they be presents!?
Dagger: N... No they're not!
Furygrowl: What is this? It says An... An-something on the box. Geez, your handwriting so ugly that it's barely readable.
Dagger: Put it down!
Furygrowl: Hehe, so even blockhead like you has reached age of giving gifts to girls.

Dagger: I... I'm not giving gifts to no one!
Why would I give presents to girls anyway!?

Furygrowl: OK, OK, put me down. Stop shaking me!
If so, then you tell me what those boxes are.
Dagger: Th... These are just trash I throwing out later.
Furygrowl: Is that so?
Dagger: O.... of course! Do I look like someone who hand out presents!?

Furygrowl: I figure as much. You're like the last person I expect to get present from. I'll be going to training grounds first and wait for you there.
You can come after you're done throwing out the trash.

Dagger: Forget about it... 
I'm not the type to hand out presents at all...
